CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 7, 1964, pg. 6 reads:"Hilton Crowded for Brotherhood Food Festival - Deltas Win First - The table of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority won first prize at the Brotherhood Food Festival, sponsored by the Pittsburgh Council of Negro Woman, at the Hilton Hotel last Saturday. Delta sorors shown are (left to right) Ruth Lee, Florence May, Nancy Lee, Lula Howell, cochairman, Vivian Swain and Maria Lawrence.  Using bread from all countries, their theme was "Let Us Break Bread Together." - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of members of the Delta Sigma Theta sorority, left to right, Ruth Lee, Florence May, Nancy Lee, Lula Howell, Vivian Swain, and Maria Lawrence, standing behind rectangular banquet table with desserts, sign reading "Delta Sigma Theta Sorority",  and globe with sign inscribed "1st Prize", in Hilton Hotel for Brotherhood Food Festival
